The Letter of Peter to Philip

Nag Hammadi Library VIII/II, The Letter of Peter to Philip

English Translation by Frederik Wisse
Interlinear translation by Milan Konvicka, 8. Jul 2011, latest update: 22. May 2012

  • translation
  • interlinear
  • coptic text

translation

(132/10)-(132/11)The Letter of Peter which he sent to Philip
(132/12)-(132/15)"Peter, the apostle of Jesus Christ, to Philip, our beloved brother and our fellow apostle, and (to) the brethren who are with you: greetings!
(132/16)-(132/19)Now I want you to know, our brother, that we received orders from our Lord and the Savior of the whole world
(132/19)-(133/1)that we should come together to give instruction and preach in the salvation which was promised us by our Lord Jesus Christ.
(133/1)-(133/3)But as for you, you were separate from us, and you did not desire us to come together
(133/4)-(133/5)and to know how we should organize ourselves in order that we might tell the good news.
(133/6)-(133/8)Therefore would it be agreeable to you, our brother, to come according to the orders of our God Jesus?"
(133/8)-(133/11)When Philip had received these (words), and when he had read them, he went to Peter rejoicing with gladness.
(133/12)-(133/15)Then Peter gathered the others also. They went upon the mountain which is called "the (mount) olives,"
(133/15)-(133/17)the place where they used to gather with the blessed Christ when he was in the body.
(133/17)-(133/21)Then, when the apostles had come together, and had thrown themselves upon their knees, they prayed thus saying,
(133/21)-(133/26)"Father, Father, Father of the light, who possesses the incorruptions, hear us just as thou hast taken pleasure in thy holy child Jesus Christ.
(133/26)-(134/1)For he became for us an illuminator in the darkness. Yea hear us!"
(134/2)-(134/3)And they prayed again another time, saying,
(134/3)-(134/6)"Son of life, Son of immortality, who is in the light,
(134/6)-(134/7)Son, Christ of immortality, our Redeemer,
(134/8)-(134/9)give us power, for they seek to kill us!"
(134/9)-(134/13)Then a great light appeared so that the mountains shone from the sight of him who had appeared.
(134/13)-(134/14)And a voice called out to them saying,
(134/15)-(134/16)"Listen to my words that I may speak to you.
(134/16)-(134/18)Why are you asking me? I am Jesus Christ who am with you forever."
(134/18)-(134/20)Then the apostles answered and said,
(134/20)-(134/23)"Lord, we would like to know the deficiency of the aeons and their pleroma."
(134/23)-(134/24)And: "How are we detained in this dwelling place?"
(134/25)-(134/26)Further: "How did we come to this place?" And: "In what manner shall we depart?"
(134/26)-(135/1)Again: "How do we have the authority of boldness?"
(135/2)And: "Why do the powers fight against us?"
(135/3)-(135/4)Then a voice came to them out of the light saying,
(135/4)-(135/6)"It is you yourselves who are witnesses that I spoke all these things to you.
(135/7)-(135/8)But because of your unbelief I shall speak again.
(135/8)-(135/10)First of all concerning the deficiency of the aeons, this is the deficiency,
(135/10)-(135/14)when the disobedience and the foolishness of the mother appeared without the commandment of the majesty of the Father.
(135/14)-(135/17)She wanted to raise up aeons. And when she spoke, the Arrogant One followed.
(135/17)-(135/21)And when she left behind a part, the Arrogant One laid hold of it, and it became a deficiency. This is the deficiency of the aeons.
(135/21)-(135/24)Now when the Arrogant One had taken a part, he sowed it. And he placed powers over it and authorities.
(135/25)-(135/28)And he enclosed it in the aeons which are dead. And all the powers of the world rejoiced that they had been begotten.
(135/28)-(136/3)But they do not know the pre-existent Father, since they are strangers to him.
(136/3)-(136/5)But this is the one to whom they gave power and whom they served by praising him.
(136/5)-(136/7)But he, the Arrogant One, became proud on account of the praise of the powers.
(136/7)-(136/11)He became an envier and he wanted to make an image in the place of an image, and a form in the place of a form.
(136/11)-(136/13)And he commissioned the powers within his authority to mold mortal bodies.
(136/13)-(136/15)And they came to be from a misrepresentation, from the semblance which had merged."
(136/16)-(136/18)"Next concerning the pleroma: I am the one who was sent down in the body because of the seed which had fallen away.
(136/19)-(136/20)And I came down into their mortal mold.
(136/20)-(136/22)But they did not recognize me; they were thinking of me that I was a mortal man.
(136/22)-(136/23)And I spoke with him who belongs to me,
(136/23)-(136/25)and he harkened to me just as you too who harkened today.
(136/26)-(136/28)And I gave him authority in order that he might enter into the inheritance of his fatherhood.
(136/28)-(137/2)And I took [...] they were filled [...] in his salvation.
(137/2)-(137/3)And since he was a deficiency,
(137/3)-(137/4)for this reason he became a pleroma."
(137/4)-(137/6)"It is because of this that you are being detained, because you belong to me.
(137/6)-(137/9)When you strip off from yourselves what is corrupted, then you will become illuminators in the midst of mortal men."
(137/10)-(137/13)"And this (is the reason) that you will fight against the powers, because they do not have rest like you, since they do not wish that you be saved."
(137/13)-(137/17)Then the apostles worshiped again saying, "Lord, tell us: In what way shall we fight against the archons, since the archons are above us?"
(137/17)-(137/21)Then a voice called out to them from the appearance saying, "Now you will fight against them in this way,
(137/21)-(137/23)for the archons are fighting against the inner man. And you are to fight against them in this way:
(137/23)-(137/25)Come together and teach in the world the salvation with a promise.
(137/25)-(137/27)And you, gird yourselves with the power of my Father,
(137/27)-(137/29)and let your prayer be known. And he, the Father, will help you
(137/29)-(138/1)as he has helped you by sending me.
(138/2)-(138/3)Be not afraid, I am with you forever, as I previously said to you when I was in the body."
(138/3)-(138/5)Then there came lightning and thunder from heaven,
(138/5)-(138/7)and what appeared to them in that place was taken up to heaven.
(138/7)-(138/10)Then the apostles gave thanks to the Lord with every blessing. And they returned to Jerusalem.
(138/10)-(138/13)And while coming up they spoke with each other on the road concerning the light which had come.
(138/13)-(138/15)And a remark was made concerning the Lord. It was said,
(138/15)-(138/16)"If he, our Lord, suffered, then how much (must) we (suffer)?"
(138/17)-(138/18)Peter answered saying,
(138/18)-(138/20)"He suffered on our behalf, and it is necessary for us too to suffer because of our smallness."
(138/21)-(138/22)Then a voice came to them saying,
(138/22)-(138/24)"I have told you many times: it is necessary for you to suffer.
(138/24)-(138/27)It is necessary that they bring you to synagogues and governors, so that you will suffer.
(138/27)-(139/1)But he who does not suffer and does not [...]
(139/2)-(139/3)[...] the Father
(139/4)-(139/5)[...] in order that he may [...]."
(139/5)-(139/7)And the apostles rejoiced greatly and came up to Jerusalem.
(139/7)-(139/9)And they came up to the temple and gave instruction in salvation in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ.
(139/9)-(139/10)And they healed a multitude.
(139/10)-(139/13)And Peter opened his mouth, he said to his (fellow) disciples, "Did our Lord Jesus, when he was in the body, show us everything?
(139/13)-(139/15)For he came down. My brothers, listen to my voice." And he was filled with a holy spirit.
(139/16)-(139/17)He spoke thus: "Our illuminator, Jesus, came down and was crucified.
(139/17)-(139/19)And he bore a crown of thorns. And he put on a purple garment.
(139/19)-(139/21)And he was crucified on a tree and he was buried in a tomb.
(139/21)-(139/23)And he rose from the dead. My brothers, Jesus is a stranger to this suffering.
(139/23)-(139/24)But we are the ones who have suffered through the transgression of the mother.
(139/25)-(139/26)And because of this, he did everything like us.
(139/26)-(139/29)For the Lord Jesus, the Son of the immeasurable glory of the Father, he is the author of our life.
(139/29)-(140/1)My brothers, let us therefore not obey these lawless ones, and walk in [...]."
(140/2)-(140/3)[...] Then Peter gathered together the others also,
(140/3)-(140/7)saying, "O, Lord Jesus Christ, author of our rest, give us a spirit of understanding in order that we also may perform wonders."
(140/7)-(140/10)Then Peter and the other apostles saw him, and they were filled with a holy spirit,
(140/10)-(140/13)And each one performed healings. And they parted in order to preach the Lord Jesus.
(140/13)-(140/15)And they came together and greeted each other saying, "Amen."
(140/15)-(140/19)Then Jesus appeared saying to them, "Peace to you all and everyone who believes in my name.
(140/19)-(140/21)And when you depart, joy be to you and grace and power.
(140/21)-(140/23)And be not afraid; behold, I am with you forever."
(140/23)-(140/26)Then the apostles parted from each other into four words in order to preach.
(140/26)-(140/27)And they went by a power of Jesus, in peace.
